      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# Lets get you out of div 3\n\nFirst thing to note is i will be basing qual of eu qual which is top 100\n\n# Estimated qual\nThe estimated qual is around 315-325  points (325 points to be safe)\n\nKey Priorities\n\nAlright you made it to div 3 and now are looking for the big div 2 to really show yourself you can do this. I will be helping you here to achieve that!\n\nBy now you MUST have a set drop spot as you need to know your offspawn place like the back of your hand for the tricks and stuff you can do offspawn to win. EVERY GAME COUNTS!\n\nNow you need to improve that mental of yours. I see wayyyyyy too many teams after a bad 1st game be down or want to give up. You can have 4 bad games all at the start and then have 6 good games all at the end. Every game is its OWN independent event, do not let what happened last game affect your mentality and make bad calls etc. You need to treat each game as a new opportunity and you must always GAME TO win, I do not want to hear anymore of this bullshit “bro this game we need 30 points then next game 20 points” stop planning for failures plan to come first and win every game.\n\nFurthermore you need to be aware of what is going on in endgame. I see way too many players sitting backside when they can rotate etc looking for a “refresh” when they have capped builds. Like come on if you’re capped out and ready to win the game there’s no point sitting backside when everyone has rotated looking for one kill, lock in and rotate. (Please note if you have some strategy etc where you sit back late jetpack this is an exception ofc, just to point out to not waste a good position for 1 kill point.)\n\nIn addition I need you guys playing deadside of moving zones. I do NOT see enough people talk about this, all the info about this secret topic is provided in #⭕・deadside.\n\nNow in midgame you need to be prioritising smart plays that will set you up for endgame, not braindead keys nor 1000 km rotates for no reason.",
